cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.CG, cs.MM, cs.RO 

The paper deals with 3D volumetric reconstruction using multi-view stereo and photometric imaging techniques, which are commonly used in computer vision and graphics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves geometric modeling and optimization, which are relevant to cs.GR (Computer Graphics) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Additionally, the use of multiple images from multiple points of view suggests the possibility of applications in robotics and automation, which are related to cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
